
<Lesson stage="3" page="5" type="Reading Check">
<APageParagraph activityIntroClip="uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3"  pencil="p3" skipIntro="true">
   <paragraph>
      <sentence>
		  <text>CR</text>
		  <clip></clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
         <text>Thomas Edison’s first recording machine was a simple sort of thing.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>It used a roll of metal to record on.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
       <sentence>
         <text>He spoke a few words of a nursery rhyme into it, and then set it to play back to him.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>The funny, squeaky voice on the machine spoke to him quite clearly.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>It said, "Mary had a little lamb, its fleece was white as snow."</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>That was well over a hundred years ago in 1877.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
  </paragraph>
  <paragraph>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>CR</text>
		  <clip></clip>
	  </sentence>
    <sentence>
		  <text>CR</text>
		  <clip></clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
         <text>He competed with others to be the first to design and build a machine that could record and play back sound.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>Edison got there first.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
  </paragraph>
  <paragraph>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>      
	    <sentence>
         <text>Edison is, of course, famous for other inventions.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>He never stopped making things.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>He made an electric light bulb, and switches and fuses.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>He also designed a machine which could make electric power.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>He spent a lot of time improving the working of the telephone and the telegraph.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
		  </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>He helped to design cameras for film-making.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
   </paragraph>
   <paragraph>
       <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>   
      <sentence>
         <text>He played a part in the invention of the typewriter.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
       <sentence>
         <text>He designed new ways to improve the making of cement and concrete.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>He build an electric train.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>He was still hard at work and full of new ideas when he was 80 years old.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
   </paragraph>
   <paragraph>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>CR</text>
         <clip></clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>One of the most amazing things about Thomas Edison was that he had no training as a scientist.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>He had great problems learning in school and left early, without a diploma.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>He was self-taught after that.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
         <text>He is one of a very few such men in history.</text>
         <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
	  </sentence>
	  <sentence>
		  <text>They were men who had a kind of genius for inventing things.</text>
		  <clip>uk/assets/sound/whiteSpace.mp3</clip>
      </sentence>
   </paragraph>
</APageParagraph>
</Lesson>
